# Black-only UI (Contract)

## Summary
- Root: `<html class="theme-dark">` in the layout.
- Load a single global stylesheet (e.g., `styles.css`).
- Forbid hard-coded colors (`#fff`, `rgb()`, `hsl()`, gradients).
- Colors must come only from tokens defined in `styles.css`.

## Required tokens and primitives (add to styles.css)
```css
:root.theme-dark {
  --bg: #000000;
  --fg: #fafafa;
  --card: #0a0a0a;
  --border: #1a1a1a;
  --accent: #ffffff; /* links, primary buttons */
  --accent-fg: #000000;
}

html.theme-dark, body { background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg); }
.card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
a { color: var(--accent); }
.btn-primary { background: var(--accent); color: var(--accent-fg); }
```
